Motivation

Tracking markers only may fail when the assumed probability distribution fails to describe the markers' complex trajectories. Three markers trajectories are visualized in the interactive figure. Their 3D positions and 2D positions on the CBCT detector are plotted. We can see inhalation trajectories overlap exhalation trajectories on the 2D detector, which may confuse the assumed probability distribution.

Results

Predicting Volumetric Images


4DCT with 10 discrete phases Interpolating images Interpolating DDFs Interpolating surrogates
The above video compares the motion dynamics of 3 different methods: (1) interpolating volumetric images; (2) interpolating Dense Displacement Fields (DDFs); (3) interpolating the surrogate states. NuTracker could produce continuous and accurate lung motion for phantom and real patients.

Predicting Segmentation for Tumor, Markers and OARs

A small add-on neural network enables NuTracker to predict segmentation masks. Left: ground-truth 4DCT and segmentation; Right: predicted 4DCT and segmentation. We also observe that the tumor deformation is more significant than fiducial markers (blue and red) during respiration, which suggests that tracking markers only may not fully capture the tumor deformation.
